    "Of note, AML-MR defining karyotypes (complex karyotypes or monosomy 7) or somatic mutations were found broadly in various clusters (Extended Data Fig. 8b-d), suggesting that these alterations do not define specific categories.",
    "By contrast, ETV6 and RUNX1 alterations not defining established categories were found preferentially in clusters associated with FAB M0/1 or immature or T cell-like signatures (Fig. 6d, Extended Data Fig.",
    "8b-d and Supplementary Table 21), as previously described 59.",
    "Although various ETV6 or RUNX1 alterations can be class-defining (for example, RUNX1::RUNX1T1) or co-occur with other defining alterations, those in the Unclassified category are commonly loss-of-function (Lower) Frequency of FAB classification (blue bars) and karyotype (gray bars) in individual categories.",
    "b, Mutational heatmap showing mutation frequencies in each molecular category."
